# Glitchbyte

Programmer unlocking secrets of the universe.

I mostly work in Rust and C, with projects that lean toward systems programming, low-level tooling, Nintendo 64 and retro game development, and learning by building.

## What I work on

- [learn_rust_with_tests](https://github.com/0xGlitchbyte/learn_rust_with_tests) — learning Rust through test-driven development
- [gblib](https://github.com/0xGlitchbyte/gblib) — my personal C codebase and library
- [N64devkit](https://github.com/0xGlitchbyte/N64devkit) — a devcontainer-based C toolkit for Nintendo 64 development
- [TinyNightmare64](https://github.com/0xGlitchbyte/TinyNightmare64) — an actually-started N64 game jam project
- [OCrab](https://github.com/0xGlitchbyte/OCrab) — a Rust-to-OCaml translator aimed at low-level bindings work

